Floods kill 16 in China ' s Jiangxi - paper . Floods caused by torrential rain in southeastern China ' s Jiangxi province have killed 16 people in recent days , the pro - Beijing newspaper Ta Kung Pao said on Sunday . The flooding destroyed 26 , 000 houses , hitting more than 340 , 000 hectares ( 850 , 000 acres ) of farmland and affecting 5 . 59 million people in the province , the newspaper said . Deluges also forced the suspension of train services from eastern China ' s Shanghai to Fuzhou and Xiamen in southeastern Fujian province , the report said . Floods across much of southern and eastern China have killed at least 85 people this month , state media and officials said on Friday . 
